What you need to know:

Chespol, the 2019 winner, makes a return after missing the last two editions owing to an injury while Aprot, the 2018 champion hopes to reclaim the crown after finishing fourth on return last yearChespol competed in seven events last year on return from injury, which included her 3,000m steeplechase victory at the Absa Kip Keino Classic on September 18 at the Moi International Sports Centre, KasaraniThe 2016 Africa Cross Country bronze medallist Charles Mneria eyes a fourth consecutive title in the men's 10km race where he faces a horde of seasoned long distance athletes